As the 2010s draw to a close, here are key ways the country looks different from 10 years ago:From smartphones to social media, tech use has become the norm.
As of 2019, nine-in-ten U.S. adults say they go online, 81% say they own a smartphone and 72% say they use social media.
Social media is now a key pathway to news for Americans.
In 2018, for the first time, social media sites surpassed print newspapers as a news source for Americans.
One-in-five adults said they often get news from social media, slightly higher than the share who often did so from print newspapers (16%).